The First Family will celebrate their first Christmas in the White House with a theme called "Time-Honored Traditions." The decorations include a Gold Star Family Tree in the East Wing, a China Room set up for a family Christmas dinner, and the Library featuring President Franklin D. Roosevelt's edition of "A Christmas Carol." The State Floor showcases the first themed White House Christmas, the "Nutcracker Suite" in 1961, and the official White House Christmas tree in the Blue Room is decorated with glass ornaments representing each State and territory. The Red Room features holiday treats, and the State Dining Room has a gingerbread house depicting the South facade of the White House. First Lady Melania Trump expressed her excitement for their first Christmas in the White House and wished everyone a Merry Christmas and joyous holiday season. The White House will host open houses, receptions, and public tours throughout December.